frus:attachment.p:
Article 1. It is harmless, unnecessary, inasmuch as Paraguay and Bolivia are adherents to the Pact of the League of Nations Treaties, Conventions, etc., Between the United States of America and Other Powers, 1910–1923 (Washington, Government Printing Office, 1923), vol. iii, p. 3336. which covers the point in the article; to the Kellogg-Briand Pact;
Foreign Relations, 1928, vol. i, p. 153. to the Gondra Treaty;
Ibid., 1923, vol. i, p. 308; see also ibid., 1928, vol. i, pp. 644 ff. and likewise the same obligation is contracted by both countries in the Díaz Léon-Gutiérrez Protocol of 1927,Signed April 22, 1927; for text, see despatch No. 275, April 29, 1927, from the Chargé in Argentina, ibid., 1927, vol. i, p. 316. and in the final act of the Conferences of Buenos Aires of July, 1928,
Ibid., 1928, vol. i, p. 675. all of which, nevertheless, have not prevented military incidents in the fortines of the Chaco, and the repeated threats of aggression on the part of Bolivia. In spite of the above, Paraguay accepts article 1.
